{
  "texts": [
    "RARO relies on the critic performing explicit CoT reasoning before providing a final judgment.",
    "When this reasoning step is removed, the critic loses its capacity to make meaningful distinctions between responses.",
    "As shown in Figure 11, instead of providing consistent signals, it collapses into a degenerate state, consistently outputting a tie response regardless of the quality of the policy or expert answer.",
    "This failure prevents the policy from receiving useful reward signals, stalling learning.",
    "Importance of Relativistic Setup."
  ]
}